        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Codex/fix 94979 kimi web search baseurl",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n[AI-assisted] Fix Moonshot/Kimi `web_search` authentication failures when the chat provider is configured to use a non-default Moonshot host.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Kimi web search only inherited `models.providers.moonshot.baseUrl` in a narrower set of cases. That could send web search traffic to the wrong endpoint and produce `401 Invalid Authentication`, even when the same API key already worked for Moonshot chat completions.\r\n\r\nThis change makes Kimi web search reuse the configured Moonshot base URL whenever one is present, so chat and web search stay aligned.\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n- Updated Kimi web search base URL resolution to inherit `models.providers.moonshot.baseUrl` directly when configured.\r\n- Kept explicit `tools.web.search.kimi.baseUrl` overrides working as before.\r\n- Added a regression test for inherited non-default Moonshot base URLs.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/moonshot/src/kimi-web-search-provider.test.ts`\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- **Behavior addressed:** Kimi `web_search` should authenticate successfully when Moonshot chat already works with the same API key and a configured non-default Moonshot host.\r\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw workspace on this machine.\r\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/moonshot/src/kimi-web-search-provider.test.ts`\r\n- **Evidence after fix:** The targeted Moonshot/Kimi web-search test file passed, including the regression coverage for inherited base URL handling.\r\n- **Observed result after fix:** 15 tests passed in the Moonshot Kimi web search provider lane.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThis fixes the regression reported in #94979 where Kimi web search returned `401 Invalid Authentication` even with a valid key that already worked for Moonshot chat completions.",
